title: Frank Lloyd Wright Saguaro Forms Earrings
description:
The landscape of Arizona influenced Frank Lloyd Wright’s designs. The saguaro cactus with its massive arms and barrel trunk becomes an element for play in his unrealized artwork for a Liberty magazine cover, “Saguaro Forms and Cactus Flowers.” 1927.

Details:

• Solid brass

• Electro-plated with non-tarnishing silver finish

• Giclee print

• Glass beads

• Ear wires are hypo-allergenic

• Hangs approx. 1.75"
